100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 4, 1925, the world witnessed significant developments, including the continued tensions in the Near East as Turkey and Greece engaged in diplomatic discussions regarding territorial disputes. In the United States, the Senate debated the future of Prohibition, with increasing calls for reform as public sentiment shifted. Meanwhile, in the realm of science, news of advancements in radio technology captured public interest, promising to revolutionize communication further.
